ALEX Salmond and Nicola Sturgeon are covering all seven Scottish cities today, campaigning for a Yes vote. SNP top two on seven-city trail ALEX Salmond and Nicola Sturgeon are covering all seven Scottish cities today, campaigning for a Yes vote.Mr Salmond will be in Aberdeen, Inverness and Dundee while the Deputy First Minister will be starting in Drumchapel in Glasgow with actors Martin Compston and Peter Mullan.She will then move on to Edinburgh and Stirling.The First Minister and Deputy First Minister will later arrive in Perth where both will meet Yes activists. 